Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.85,0:00:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.56,0:00:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.56,0:00:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.81,0:00:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.11,0:00:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.62,0:00:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.58,0:00:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.47,0:01:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.60,0:01:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.02,0:01:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With a body already ridden with injuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.75,0:01:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} went on to have a Duel with Mai.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.73,0:01:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though he was using all his might to remove the darkness in Mai's heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.67,0:01:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...he lost his own soul in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.97,0:01:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The man manipulating Mai and the Musketeers...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.59,0:01:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the true enemy who captured the souls of Partner and Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.24,0:01:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dartz!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.56,0:01:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.38,0:02:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Duel of Destiny! \NYugi VS Rafael"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.92,0:02:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.10,0:02:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.89,0:02:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.19,0:02:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You jerk...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.69,0:02:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His soul is also...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.24,0:02:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who could have...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.23,0:02:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been Mai.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was searching for Jounouchi and Varon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.16,0:02:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.86,0:02:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.50,0:02:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! I won't forgive Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.76,0:02:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.36,0:02:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truly unforgivable one is our true enemy who's been controlling the Musketeers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.24,0:02:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.24,0:03:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.81,0:03:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Mai...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Harpy's feather...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:03:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.54,0:04:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you {\i1}were{\i0} the one behind this, Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.37,0:04:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for you, Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.66,0:05:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.67,0:05:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s Claw of Hermos!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who took down Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0} and Mai!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.99,0:05:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who defeated Jounouchi was Mai Kujaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.16,0:05:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.63,0:05:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why is Mai also...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.08,0:05:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Mai foolishly decided to rebel against Lord Dartz!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.92,0:05:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've got no business with {\i0}you{\i1}, Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where is Dartz?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've got no more need for the power of Doma or the Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.02,0:05:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to use my own abilities to defeat Dartz!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That way I can take responsibility for my actions against Jounouchi and Varon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do not be conceited, Mai Kujaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.92,0:05:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the end, you were nothing more than an additional offering on the list!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.25,0:05:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.37,0:05:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You act far too much on your own agenda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And you've run out of chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be good and disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.37,0:05:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.20,0:06:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jou...nou...chi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s feelings finally reached Mai.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But despite that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both Jounouchi and Mai probably hoped that this card would end up in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, you should hold on to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you feel any pain at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.43,0:06:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't your heart throb? Doesn't your chest ache?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.98,0:06:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.08,0:06:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.95,0:06:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuzaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.37,0:06:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.98,0:06:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.19,0:06:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how many souls have you taken away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Amelda and Varon...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.20,0:06:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the souls of your {\i1}companions{\i0} were taken away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even despite that, you don't feel anything at {\i1}all{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.81,0:06:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've said this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.95,0:07:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That nothing can be achieved while humans liter this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.83,0:07:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why destiny {\i1}exists{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.27,0:07:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in order to understand your destiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can only accept it and offer yourself to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.18,0:07:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also want to know the answer my destiny offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.06,0:07:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I won't hesitate to offer my soul and my very life in the process!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would a Duelist of your caliber need to abide by the destiny set up by Dartz?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.49,0:07:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the purpose of having souls unique to {\i1}ourselves{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.17,0:07:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destiny has already begun to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.35,0:07:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pages of this era have already begun flipping into the next chapter!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one can stop the wheels of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.44,0:07:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is... that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stars... are disappearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.21,0:08:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on, Honda!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.93,0:08:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honda! Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.40,0:08:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn deadbeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've lost as well...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.82,0:08:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.28,0:08:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.77,0:08:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He set off for Paradias Organization alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Mokuba?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Th-That...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rats!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quick, get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is going {\i1}on{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.42,0:09:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The great doors of Destiny will be opened by Lord Dartz.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.61,0:09:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only then will our answers reveal themselves before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.19,0:09:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of that day, Pharaoh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will fight against you once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.02,0:09:56.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did defeat you that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.12,0:10:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who lose to The Barrier of Orichalcos will have their souls taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your soul was not taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know why destiny made this arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But compared to the destiny Lord Dartz speaks of...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.69,0:10:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it becomes insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.67,0:10:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is right. You will not be able to defeat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.92,0:10:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will prove right now that is what destiny has determined!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.60,0:10:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.12,0:10:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why must we be bounded by destiny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I too want to Duel with you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.47,0:10:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's because you are a True Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.14,0:10:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has {\i1}nothing{\i0} to do with destiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.78,0:10:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, our Duel was predetermined by fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.57,0:10:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for that, I must get your soul this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.89,0:10:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.10,0:11:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your destiny lies here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let your hands decide your own destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you pass that barrier card to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.59,0:11:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not use it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.81,0:11:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.12,0:11:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This time I want him to use his own hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...to destroy The Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.05,0:11:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll attack first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.04,0:12:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.77,0:12:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look out, Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.86,0:12:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will unleash my battle tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.17,0:12:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuous Magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure of Guardian God!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Treasure of Guardian God...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.83,0:12:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}By discarding the five cards he has in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.15,0:12:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...he can draw two cards from his deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.34,0:12:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He can also draw two cards in his subsequent turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is a card that allows one to draw more cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.14,0:12:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I Summon Backup Gardna in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card and complete my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.56,0:12:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Queen's Knight in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.36,0:12:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.40,0:12:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If he really plans to use The Barrier of Orichalcos...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.39,0:12:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...when will he play it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.77,0:13:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.99,0:13:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My companions are pleased to be able to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.07,0:13:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I send you greetings on their behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.28,0:13:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuous Magic! Gravity Axe!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.23,0:13:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the special effect of Gravity Axe...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.64,0:13:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Special Summon Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the Effect of Backup Gardna...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.64,0:13:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gravity Axe will be equipped onto Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.10,0:13:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Guardian Grarl!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swift Cleave Attack!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.72,0:13:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.07,0:13:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.51,0:13:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use the Magic Card, Resurrection of the Dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.32,0:13:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to revive Queen's Knight in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then from my hand, I Summon King's Knight in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then activate the Special Effect of King's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When King's Knight and Queen's Knight are both on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.48,0:14:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...one Jack's Knight can be Special Summoned from the deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, a Magic Card! Brave Attack, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That card...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.54,0:14:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next I activate\N a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Brave Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.84,0:14:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Magnet Warriors!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.59,0:14:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.27,0:14:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card that defeated the god, Dark Obelisk!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.46,0:14:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Brave Attack can combine all the Attack Points of my Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It allows my Monsters to defeat a single enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for a chance to do so!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you already forgotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you lost the previous battle because you sacrificed your Monsters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:14:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.92,0:15:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be swayed by your words any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in the bonds I have with my Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.02,0:15:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We share both pain and joy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.71,0:15:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, Knights!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.81,0:15:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show him your combined power!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.56,0:15:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian Force!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.10,0:15:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can only be activated when there are no Guardian Monsters in the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.43,0:15:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can destroy a Magic Card that set up the incoming battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.43,0:15:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can easily destroy such low level tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.76,0:15:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.37,0:15:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Indeed, his tactics are impregnable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.64,0:15:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And above all, if he decides to activate The Barrier of Orichalcos...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.35,0:15:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.87,0:16:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But, I can't imagine him using that barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.21,0:16:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I didn't actually believe he'd play it the last time either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.37,0:16:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Equipment Magic, Butterfly Dagger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.60,0:16:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attack of the Monster equipped with it goes up by 300 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.31,0:16:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guided by the Butterfly Dagger is my Guardian Monster known as Elma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A new Guardian Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.98,0:16:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Special Effect of Guardian Elma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.20,0:16:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Equipment Magic Card from the Graveyard can be equipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Equip Guardian Shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, The Special Effect of Backup Gardna...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.26,0:16:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Butterfly Dagger is equipped onto Guardian Elma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.59,0:16:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian Elma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.71,0:16:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Queen's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.56,0:16:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despair Confusion!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, Guardian Grarl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:16:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack King's Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.51,0:17:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swift Cleave Attack!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's strong enough even without relying on the Barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.12,0:17:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.99,0:17:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I only have one Five-Star Monster on my field.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.23,0:17:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate Twinkle Five Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.60,0:17:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A new Monster is Summoned by using the five stars of Jack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear! The Five Kuriboh Siblings!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've sent out the shrimps again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.17,0:17:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By discarding one Trap Card from my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.52,0:17:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Special Effect of Kuribu!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.82,0:17:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out! Kuriball!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attack Power of Grarl...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.13,0:18:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Special Ability of Kuriball!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.85,0:18:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In just this turn, it can cause the Attack of the targeted Monster to drop by 1500 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And because of the Special Ability of Kuriba...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.61,0:18:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Five Kuriboh Brothers combine into one to form Kuribabylon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.27,0:18:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.47,0:18:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian Grarl's Attack Power is also 1500!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.97,0:18:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The preparations for this fight aren't finished yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.90,0:18:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate the Magic Card, Cyclone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.04,0:18:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.27,0:18:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can destroy one Magic or Trap Card on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy Gravity Axe!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.63,0:18:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Kuribabylon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.07,0:18:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.96,0:18:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.02,0:19:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate the special effect of Guardian Shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.27,0:19:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the shield is destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.25,0:19:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can prevent a Monster from getting destroyed during battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.04,0:19:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still take damage as per the enemy's strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He protects his Monsters at the expense of his Life...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.42,0:19:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right... That is how you fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.63,0:19:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The determination not to send any Monsters into the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.82,0:19:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Monsters and their respective player's mutual bonds to protect each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.41,0:19:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It goes to prove that you're not the kind of Duelist who would activate The Barrier of Orichalcos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.35,0:19:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your ideals regarding Duels...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is surely not in line with The Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.73,0:19:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of protecting your Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.48,0:19:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you will not give in to the darkness in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.10,0:19:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Rafael?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.00,0:19:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pharaoh, you are right about what you just said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.00,0:19:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.81,0:20:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that is correct, it's not sufficient to understand the answer to destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.92,0:20:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you accept the darkness in your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.62,0:20:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and it becomes part of you when you give up everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.29,0:20:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Light appears in the darkness for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.77,0:20:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a much larger destiny is born as a result!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.69,0:20:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.74,0:20:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are very alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.12,0:20:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we chose very different routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.62,0:20:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you cannot utilize your strength fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.08,0:20:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, I'll show it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.23,0:20:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real strength behind this card!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.00,0:20:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.59,0:20:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier of Orichalcos!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.78,0:20:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.50,0:20:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.56,0:20:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.43,0:20:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mai-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:21:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.29,0:21:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Mai got...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.19,0:21:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rooftop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.50,0:21:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.67,0:21:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.94,0:21:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.52,0:22:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.88,0:22:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.49,0:22:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.56,0:22:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.04,0:22:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.32,0:22:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.22,0:22:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.37,0:23:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.89,0:23:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.27,0:23:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was waiting for Yugi at Paradias...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.62,0:23:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was Rafael, who had defeated Yugi previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.15,0:23:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he's an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.07,0:23:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi respects the way Rafael treats his Monsters during his Duels.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.98,0:23:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, Yugi is bewildered when he activated The Barrier of Orichalcos.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.59,0:23:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, he Summons Guardian Eatos which resulted in Yugi's defeat last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.69,0:23:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.23,0:23:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.85,0:23:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Immortal! Guardian Deathscythe"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.02,0:23:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
